oracle.pg.rdbms

Class OraclePgqlExecution

  • java.lang.Object
    • oracle.pg.rdbms.OraclePgqlExecution
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.AutoCloseable, OraclePgqlPreparedStatement, OraclePgqlStatement

    public class OraclePgqlExecution
extends java.lang.Object
implements OraclePgqlPreparedStatement
    This class implements the OraclePgqlStatement and OraclePgqlPreparedStatement interfaces for executing PGQL queries against graphs stored in Oracle Database.

    Refer to the documentation of these interfaces for further explanation and sample code.

      • executeQuery

        public OraclePgqlResultSet executeQuery(int timeout,
                                        int parallel,
                                        long queryID,
                                        int dynamicSampling,
                                        int maxResults,
                                        java.lang.String options)
                                 throws PgqlToSqlException,
                                        oracle.pgql.lang.PgqlException,
                                        java.sql.SQLException
        Translates this instance's PGQL statement into a SQL statement and executes the SQL against this instance's property graph.

        Supported query options are:

        USE_GT_TAB=T Use the GRAPH_NAMEGT$ table instead of the GRAPH_NAMEGE$ table for evaluating edge traversals.

        USE_RW=F Use CONNECT BY instead of recursive WITH for unbounded path traversals.

        MAX_PATH_LEN=n Traverse at most n hops when evaluating unbounded path traversals.

        EDGE_SET_PARTIAL=T Fetch properties for each start and end vertex found when reading edges from the query result.

        Specified by:
        executeQuery in interface OraclePgqlPreparedStatement
        Parameters:
        timeout - the number of seconds for query execution to finish
        parallel - the degree of parallelism to use for query execution
        queryID - the query ID
        dynamicSampling - the value for dynamic sampling
        maxResults - the maximum number of rows returned
        options - additional options used to influence query translation and execution
        Returns:
        a OraclePgqlResultSet object with the result of the provided PGQL query
        Throws:
        PgqlToSqlException
        oracle.pgql.lang.PgqlException
        java.sql.SQLException

      • translateQuery

        public OraclePgqlSqlTrans translateQuery(int parallel,
                                         int dynamicSampling,
                                         int maxResults,
                                         java.lang.String options)
                                  throws PgqlToSqlException,
                                         oracle.pgql.lang.PgqlException
        Translates this instance's PGQL statement into a SQL statement.

        Supported query options are:

        USE_GT_TAB=T Use the GRAPH_NAMEGT$ table instead of the GRAPH_NAMEGE$ table for evaluating edge traversals.

        USE_RW=F Use CONNECT BY instead of recursive WITH for unbounded path traversals.

        MAX_PATH_LEN=n Traverse at most n hops when evaluating unbounded path traversals.

        EDGE_SET_PARTIAL=T Fetch properties for each start and end vertex found when reading edges from the query result.

        Specified by:
        translateQuery in interface OraclePgqlPreparedStatement
        Parameters:
        parallel - the degree of parallelism to use for query execution
        dynamicSampling - the value for dynamic sampling
        maxResults - the maximum number of rows returned
        options - additional options used to influence query translation
        Returns:
        a OraclePgqlSqlTrans object with the SQL translation and column metadata for the provided PGQL query
        Throws:
        PgqlToSqlException
        oracle.pgql.lang.PgqlException
